# Ritual Tap-to-Mine — Environment Variables
#
# For LOCAL DEV (use a local Postgres, or run via Vercel CLI env pull):
#   - Use Vercel CLI: `vercel link && vercel env pull .env.local` to get production env
#   - OR set up your own Postgres and provide DATABASE_URL + DIRECT_URL
#
# For VERCEL PRODUCTION:
#   - Auto-set by the Neon Vercel marketplace integration when you connect a Neon DB.
#   - If you prefer to manage env vars manually, paste your Neon connection strings here.
#
# Neon connection string format: postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST/DBNAME?sslmode=require

# Pooled connection (used by Prisma Client at runtime, serverless-friendly)
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@host/dbname?sslmode=require&pgbouncer=true&connect_timeout=15"

# Direct connection (used by Prisma CLI for migrations / db push)
DIRECT_URL="postgresql://user:password@host/dbname?sslmode=require"
